  "text": "For Alizarin Red staining, cells were fixed in 10% formol for 30 min and calcium-containing crystals stained by applying 2% Alizarin red solution (pH 5.3) for 1 h [CITATION_1] . After washings with tap water, pictures were taken. For calcium content quantification, separate plates were used. Cell monolayers were decalcified with 0.6 M HCl for 24 h. The following day, calcium content was quantified by the QuantiChrom™ Calcium Kit (BioAssay Systems) by reding absorbance at 612 nm using the Spectramax M5e reader (Molecular Devices).",
